<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1325">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/745.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department has following telegram from mine owners in Monterey
                            section:</p>
                        <p>[Quotes from Mr. Hanna’s August 4, 1 p.m.]</p>
                        <p>Exert best efforts to obtain immediate sending to tax collector at
                            Monterey of instructions along desired lines. Department understood from
                            information heretofore received from you that this had already been
                            done.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>